        "grammar_id": "G1",
        "title": "The 'There is / There are' Structure",
        "explanation": "The 'There is' structure is used to state the existence of something or someone. It is followed by a singular noun. For plural nouns, 'There are' is used. It is often accompanied by a prepositional phrase indicating location.",
        "examples": [
          {
            "text": "There is a refrigerator in the kitchen.",
            "translation": "厨房里有个电冰箱。"
          },
          {
            "text": "There is a table in the middle of the room.",
            "translation": "房间的中央有张桌子。"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "grammar_id": "G2",
        "title": "Prepositions of Place: 'on', 'in', 'in the middle of', 'on the right/left'",
        "explanation": "Prepositions are used to show the relationship between a noun or pronoun and other words in a sentence, often indicating location. 'On' means something is on the surface of another. 'In' means something is inside another. 'In the middle of' means at the center. 'On the right/left' indicates position relative to something.",
        "examples": [
          {
            "text": "It is on the right.",
            "translation": "它位于房间右侧。"
          },
          {
            "text": "There is a table in the middle of the room.",
            "translation": "房间的中央有张桌子。"
          },
          {
            "text": "There is a bottle on the table.",
            "translation": "桌子上有个瓶子。"
          },
          {
            "text": "There is a glass in the cupboard.",
            "translation": "碗柜里有一个玻璃杯。"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "grammar_id": "G3",
        "title": "Articles 'a' and 'the'",
        "explanation": "The indefinite article 'a' (or 'an' before a vowel sound) is used when referring to a general item or when something is mentioned for the first time. The definite article 'the' is used when referring to a specific item, or when something has been mentioned before and is now known to the listener/reader.",
        "examples": [
          {
            "text": "There is a refrigerator in the kitchen. The refrigerator is white.",
            "translation": "厨房里有个电冰箱。冰箱的颜色是白的。"
          },
          {
            "text": "Is there a book on the table? Yes, there is. Is the book red?",
            "translation": "桌子上有一本书吗？是的，有。那本书是红色的吗？"
          }
        ]
      }
